CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 6, 1961, pg. 16 reads: "World Churchmen Chat - These churchmen were among the specialists from around the world who met in Pittsburgh for the 26th annual Conference on Church Architecture, Home Missions and Church Extension, at the Penn-Sheraton Hotel. Discussing the elaborate exhibit are (left to right): Rev. S.E. Jakobsen and Rev. N.H. Gadegaard, both of Denmark; Dr. D. W. Andrews, AME Zion Church Extension secretary, Winston-Salem, N.C.; Dr. Conrad Hoyer of New York, executive of the Division of Home Missions, National Council of Churches, and Rev. E.W. Raemmerer of Bremen, Germany. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Rev. S.E. Jakobsen, Rev. N.H. Gadegaard, Dr. D. W. Andrews, Dr. Conrad Hoyer, and Rev. E.W. Raemmerer, gathered in exhibition booth in Penn Sheraton Hotel for 26th annual Conference on Church Architecture, Home Missions, and Church Extension
